         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne Botanic Gardens, ¶ 19 April 1871. ¶  ¶ For a long time, dear Professor, I have been looking out for news from you. I do not even know, if my original collection of Australian mosses, contain...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">71.04.19a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To Otto Lindberg</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">Sign. 630.1.1. <seg style="">4, Arkivet, Svenska Litteratursällskapet i Finland, Universitetsbibliotek, Helsingfors, Finland.</seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">Melbourne, im botanischen Garten</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">19/4/71.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Seit langem, bester Herr Professor, sehe ich nach Nachrichten von Ihnen aus. Ich weiss nicht einmal ob meine Original Sammlung australischer Moose welche Alles enthält was ich besitze, noch in Ihren Händen ist, und ob Sie in den Nachsendungen auch die 2 theueren Bände von Hookers Flora Tasmanica erhielten. Selbige kostete mir ohne Einband £15</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In diesem Monat habe ich nun wieder eine Menge seither erlangter Moose an Sie abgeschickt und zwar unter Obhut des ausgezeichneten Corvetten Capiteins Koltovskoy, der mit der "Haydamack" einige Tage in unserm Hafen weilte.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Unter den Moosen waren auch eine Menge Exemplare von Dawsonia Lindbergi.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Bittend doch recht bald von den Resultaten Ihrer schönen Arbeiten über meine Moose mir Auskunft zu geben und hoffend dass Sie ganz wohl sind bleibe ich der Ihre</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="">Melbourne Botanic Gardens,</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">19 April 1871.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>For a long time, dear Professor, I have been looking out for news from you. I do not even know, if my original collection of Australian mosses, containing everything I have, is still in your hands, or whether you received the two expensive volumes of Hooker's <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Flora tasmaniae</seg>
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">J. Hooker (1860).</p>
               </note> in the later consignments. They cost me £15/-/- unbound.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>This month I have sent you again a lot of mosses I acquired since, under the care of the excellent Captain Koltovskoy,<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Argus</seg> 23 March 1871, p. 6 for report of the Russian ship’s arrival and listing of the crew.</p>
               </note> who was in our harbour for a few days with the <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Haydamack</seg>.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Among the mosses were also a lot of specimens of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Dawsonia%20lindbergii">Dawsonia lindbergii</name>
               </seg>.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">cf. M to O. Lindberg, 21 February 1871 (in this edition as 71-02-21a). Name not in entry for <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Dawsonia</seg> as a name or a synonym in <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>B.O. van Zanten, 'Dawsonia' Australian Mosses Online, <ref target="http://www.anbg.gov.au/abrs/Mosses_online/Polytrichaceae_Dawsonia.pdf"
                          rend="Internet%20link"
                          style="color: #0563c1; ">
                        <seg rend="Internet%20link" style="color: #0563c1; ">http://www.anbg.gov.au/abrs/Mosses_online/Polytrichaceae_Dawsonia.pdf</seg>
                     </ref>, accessed 20 April 2022.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Asking that you will give me news very soon on your fine work on my mosses and hoping, that you are quite well, I remain your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Dawsonia%20lindbergii">Dawsonia lindbergii</name>
            </p>
         </div>
